@startuml
!include ../../../../images/common-sequence.iuml

title FireFly-Cloud Device Registration

actor "FireFly-Cloud\nAdmin" as Admin
actor "Manufacturing\nOperator" as Op

box "FireFly-Cloud"
    participant "API Gateway" as APIGW
    database DynamoDB
end box

box "FireFly Controller (ESP32)"
    participant "HW-Reg\nFirmware" as HWReg
end box

== Obtain Registration Key ==

Admin -> APIGW++ : **Create a new registration key**\nPOST /registration-keys\n""{visual-token}""
APIGW -> DynamoDB++ : **Store key with 30-minute TTL**\n""key = "ABC123", ttl = now+1800, used = false""
DynamoDB --> APIGW-- : OK
APIGW --> Admin-- : HTTP 201\n""{ "key": "ABC123" }""
Admin -> Op : **Share registration key with operator**\n""ABC123"" (expires in 30 min, one-time use)

== Provision Device Identity ==

Op -> HWReg++ : **Burn device identity to eFuse**\nPOST /api/identity\n""{ uuid, product_id, product_hex }""
HWReg -> HWReg : **Write UUID + master key to eFuse (irreversible)**
HWReg --> Op-- : HTTP 201 Created

== Register Device with FireFly-Cloud ==

Op -> HWReg++ : **Initiate cloud device registration**\nPOST /api/registration\n""X-Registration-Key: ABC123""\n""{ "url": "https://api.fireflylx.com" }""
HWReg -> HWReg : **Derive authentication key**\n""key_auth = HKDF-SHA256(master, "firefly-auth-v1")""
HWReg -> HWReg : **Compute P-256 public key from ""key_auth"" scalar**
HWReg -> HWReg : **Zero ""key_auth"" bytes immediately**

HWReg -> APIGW++ : **Register device in DynamoDB**\nPOST /devices/register\n""X-Registration-Key: ABC123""\n""{ uuid, public_key, device_class,""\n"" registering_application, mcu{...} }""

APIGW -> DynamoDB++ : **Look up registration key**\n""key = "ABC123""
DynamoDB --> APIGW-- : ""{ key: "ABC123", ttl, used: false }""

break Key not found, expired, or already used
    APIGW --> HWReg : HTTP 401 Unauthorized
    HWReg --> Op : HTTP 403\n""{ "message": "Invalid or expired registration key" }""
end

APIGW -> DynamoDB++ : **Write device record**\n""uuid (PK), product_hex (GSI),""\n""public_key, registration_date (immutable), ...""
DynamoDB --> APIGW-- : OK
APIGW -> DynamoDB++ : **Delete used registration key**
DynamoDB --> APIGW-- : OK
APIGW --> HWReg-- : HTTP 204 No Content
HWReg --> Op-- : HTTP 204 No Content

== Boot Status Check (runs in loop() after NTP syncs) ==

HWReg -> HWReg : **Derive ""key_auth"" and generate random nonce**
HWReg -> HWReg : **Sign nonce with ECDSA-P256 using ""key_auth""**
HWReg -> HWReg : **Zero ""key_auth"" bytes immediately**

HWReg -> APIGW++ : **Verify device registration status**\nGET /devices/{uuid}/registration\n""X-Device-UUID: {uuid}""\n""X-Device-Nonce: {base64}""\n""X-Device-Signature: {base64}""

APIGW -> DynamoDB++ : **Look up device record by UUID**
DynamoDB --> APIGW-- : Device record (includes stored public key)

alt UUID header and path param do not match
    APIGW --> HWReg : HTTP 403 Forbidden
else Signature invalid or device not found
    APIGW --> HWReg : HTTP 401 Unauthorized
else Signature valid
    APIGW --> HWReg-- : HTTP 200\n""{ registered: true, registration_date, ... }""
end

HWReg -> HWReg : **Update registration state and event log**

@enduml
